.TH TOR-SITE "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tor-site \- Create a local web server for Tor hidden services
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tor-site
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tor-site
is a script for creating and managing local web servers for Tor hidden services. It simplifies the process of hosting .onion sites.
.PP
The script handles server configuration and Tor integration for hosting hidden services.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tor-site start
Start the Tor hidden service
.TP
.B tor-site stop
Stop the service
.TP
.B tor-site status
Check service status
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/tor-site/settings.conf
User configuration file for tor-site preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
Tor not found
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Creates Tor hidden services
.IP \(bu 2
Local web server integration
.IP \(bu 2
Manages .onion addresses
